//
// ## Fork containment caveat (mt#2865 SC #4 — documented upstream limitation)
//
// This guard contains a fork's WRITES to the shared session/PR substrate —
// it does not, and structurally cannot, stop a fork from THINKING like an
// implementer (that is a harness context-scoping capability Minsky does
// not control; see mt#2512/mt#2521). The gate is only load-bearing when the
// orchestrator actually calls the dispatch-time issuance surface
